                <p><bibl><ptr target="#oliverio1928"/>, p. 326, n. <citedRange>5</citedRange>, fig. 11</bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>9.113</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>020100</citedRange></bibl>.
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#parisipresicce2007a"/>, p. <citedRange>495</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#cdlBE"/>, <citedRange>2008.602</citedRange>, p. 761</bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested"><name><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></name></persName> τ<supplied reason="lost">οῖ</supplied>ς <w lemma="θεός">θεοῖς</w> τ<supplied reason="lost">οῖς</supplied> <w>ἐ<supplied reason="lost">ν</supplied></w> τᾶι <w lemma="ἀγορά">ἀ<supplied reason="lost">γορ</supplied>ᾶι</w> <w lemma="ἀνατίθημι">ἀν<supplied reason="lost">έθηκε</supplied></w>.
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Untel fils d'Untel</supplied> a consacré aux dieux de l'agora.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">So-and-so son of So-and-so</supplied> dedicated to the gods of the agora.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Il tale figlio del tale</supplied> ha dedicato agli dèi dell'agora.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Although the stone was found re-used in the Roman Baths, its provenance is surely the agora, like <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr019900</ref> and <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr020000</ref>, 
                    see <bibl><ptr target="#cdlBE"/>, <citedRange>2008.602</citedRange>, p. 761</bibl>.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
